  "text": "A similar analysis works for low injection transients where the effective mobility can directly be identified as the minority carrier mobility in equation [CITATION_1] . However, high injection has the advantages of larger signals in the TRTS measurement, screened surface fields, and the condition Δn ≫ p 0 does not depend on the (unknown) mobilities as does the condition for low injection Δn ≪ p 0 µ p /µ n .",
